- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing techniques such as event extraction and multi-instance learning applied to a corpus of local news articles.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as the paper deals with hate crimes, which are a form of hate speech and can be considered a security issue.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper deals with extracting information from a corpus of local news articles to predict instances of hate crime.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing the local representation of hate crimes, which can be considered a social network issue.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques such as event extraction and multi-instance learning to predict instances of hate crime.
